meta {
  name: Get Node Template
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

get {
  url: {{host}}/agent-playground/node-templates/:id/
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

params:path {
  id: {{node_template_id}}
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

vars:pre-request {
  node_template_id: e9d7c212-4f51-49e0-8e0f-fc9b81a631c8
}

docs {
  # Get Node Template Detail

  Get full node template detail including port definitions and config schema.

  ## Path Parameters
  - `id`: Node Template UUID (e.g., `d523c598-1b0b-48f4-91ce-feab764e3ad4`)

  ## Response
  ```json
  {
    "status": true,
    "result": {
      "id": "d523c598-1b0b-48f4-91ce-feab764e3ad4",
      "name": "llm_prompt",
      "display_name": "LLM Prompt",
      "description": "Run a prompt against an LLM. The prompt and all LLM config live in the node config. Input ports are dynamic — users add ports for each variable referenced in the prompt messages (e.g. {{context}}, {{question}}).",
      "icon": null,
      "categories": ["llm", "ai", "prompt"],
      "input_definition": [],
      "output_definition": [
        {
          "key": "response",
          "data_schema": {"type": "string", "description": "LLM response text"}
        }
      ],
      "input_mode": "dynamic",
      "output_mode": "strict",
      "config_schema": {
        "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["model", "messages"],
        "additionalProperties": true,
        "properties": {
          "model": {
            "type": "string",
            "minLength": 1,
            "description": "LLM model identifier"
          },
          "messages": {
            "type": "array",
            "minItems": 1,
            "description": "Prompt messages with optional {{variable}} placeholders",
            "items": {
              "type": "object",
              "required": ["role", "content"],
              "additionalProperties": false,
              "properties": {
                "role": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "enum": ["system", "user", "assistant"]
                },
                "content": {"type": "string"}
              }
            }
          },
          "temperature": {
            "type": "number",
            "minimum": 0,
            "maximum": 1,
            "description": "Sampling temperature (0-1)"
          },
          "max_tokens": {
            "type": "integer",
            "minimum": 1,
            "description": "Maximum tokens in response"
          },
          "top_p": {
            "type": "number",
            "minimum": 0,
            "maximum": 1,
            "description": "Nucleus sampling parameter (0-1)"
          },
          "frequency_penalty": {
            "type": "number",
            "minimum": -2,
            "maximum": 2,
            "description": "Frequency penalty (-2 to 2)"
          },
          "presence_penalty": {
            "type": "number",
            "minimum": -2,
            "maximum": 2,
            "description": "Presence penalty (-2 to 2)"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Port Definitions
  - `input_definition`: Default input ports for nodes using this template
  - `output_definition`: Default output ports for nodes using this template
  - Each port has `key`, `data_schema`, and `required` fields

  ## Port Modes
  Port modes control which port keys are allowed on nodes using this template. Validation is enforced on publish (status="active").
  - `strict`: Only template-defined port keys are allowed. No custom ports, no arbitrary keys.
  - `extensible`: All template-defined port keys MUST be present, plus additional ports with `key="custom"` are allowed.
  - `dynamic`: All port keys must be `"custom"`. The user defines every port from scratch.

  ## Config Schema
  JSON Schema defining the configuration options for nodes using this template.
  When creating/updating nodes, the `config` object must validate against this schema.

  ## Usage
  When creating an atomic node with the LLM Prompt template:
  1. Get the template detail to understand config requirements
  2. Create the node with `node_template_id` set to this template's ID
  3. Set `config` with required `model` and `messages` fields
  4. Create **input ports** with `key="custom"` for each `{{variable}}` in your messages (dynamic input mode — all keys must be "custom"). Use `display_name` to label each port (e.g., "question").
  5. Create **output port** with key "response" (strict output mode)

  ## Example Node Config
  ```json
  {
    "model": "gpt-4",
    "messages": [
      {"role": "system", "content": "You are a helpful assistant."},
      {"role": "user", "content": "Answer this: {{question}}"}
    ],
    "temperature": 0.7
  }
  ```
  This config requires an input port with `key="custom"` and `display_name="question"` to receive the variable value.
}
